author: @BR0STRADAMUS
text: Taking breaks spoke to me on a spiritual level haha. I'm also in the CF Data Analytics course and working on my final project. I spent an hour writing a complex Python function to iterate through a large data frame and then create a new column based on seperate columns from different years in the data frame. I took a break while the function was running (it took close to 20 minutes to finish!) and during my break I realized I could just use a simple .loc method to accomplish the same task much quicker and with much less memory. Definitely a face palm moment, but taking that extra time just to think things through while eating a snack really saved a lot of time and energy for other column changes
